FL,368,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1783765122
OL,3,CEngland World Cup winner Nobby Stiles
OL,4,Cdied with brain injury, court hears
OL,6,FStiles had 28 caps for England and
OL,7,Fplayed for Manchester United nearly
OL,8,F400 times.
OL,10,FMr Morris said "for reasons not
OL,11,Fentirely clear to me" Stiles's death
OL,12,Fwas not at the time reported to the
OL,13,Fcoroner's office for investigation,
OL,14,Fwhich had only begun after information
OL,15,Fprovided by the ex-footballer's family.
OL,17,FThe coroner said Stiles's brain had
OL,18,Fbeen examined by neuropathology
OL,19,Fexpert, Dr Daniel du Plessis.
OL,26,@rD@POUsD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,368,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1783765122
OL,3,CEngland World Cup winner Nobby Stiles
OL,4,Cdied with brain injury, court hears
OL,6,FThe expert said in his opinion, after
OL,7,Freviewing Stiles's medical records,
OL,8,Fthe footballer's cause of death was
OL,9,FAlzheimer's disease.
OL,11,FBut he also said his death was
OL,12,Fcontributed to by high-stage CTE along
OL,13,Fwith what was described as "stage
OL,14,Fthree limbic predominant age related
OL,15,FTDP-43" and small vessel
OL,16,Fcerebrovascular disease.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,368,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1783765122
OL,3,CEngland World Cup winner Nobby Stiles
OL,4,Cdied with brain injury, court hears
OL,6,FMr Morris said: "On the basis of that
OL,7,Fcause of death, particularly the
OL,8,Finclusion of a traumatic injury
OL,9,Fincluded in the cause of death, I'm
OL,10,Fsatisfied an inquest is required into
OL,11,Fthe sad death of Mr Stiles."
OL,13,FAn inquest will be held on 15 July at
OL,14,FStockport Coroner's Court.
OL,16,FStiles's son John - who is head of the
OL,17,FFootball Families for Justice (FFJ)
OL,18,Fgroup - has previously said that
OL,19,Ffootball had "killed" his father.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,368,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1783765122
OL,3,CEngland World Cup winner Nobby Stiles
OL,4,Cdied with brain injury, court hears
OL,6,FHe is among multiple families and
OL,7,Fformer footballers suing the Football
OL,8,FAssociation the Football Association
OL,9,Fof Wales and the English Football
OL,10,FLeague over claims they were
OL,11,F"negligent and in breach of their duty
OL,12,Fof care" to the former players.
OL,14,FLawyers for the former players and
OL,15,Ftheir families have previously said
OL,16,Ffootball bodies knew or should have
OL,17,Fknown that repeatedly heading a ball
OL,18,Fin training and during matches was
OL,19,Flikely to cause brain injuries, and
OL,20,Fthat the risks were known for decades.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,368,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1783765122
OL,3,CEngland World Cup winner Nobby Stiles
OL,4,Cdied with brain injury, court hears
OL,6,FIn March 2026 lawyers for The Football
OL,7,FAssociation told the High Court it has
OL,8,F"not been established by science" that
OL,9,Fheading a ball or "occasional"
OL,10,Fconcussion can lead to permanent brain
OL,11,Fdamage.
OL,13,FIn January an inquest into the death
OL,14,Fof ex-Manchester United and Scotland
OL,15,Fdefender Gordon McQueen, 70, found
OL,16,Fthat heading the ball was "likely" to
OL,17,Fhave contributed to a brain injury
OL,18,Fwhich was a factor in his death.
OL,20,FMcQueen was also diagnosed with
OL,21,Fchronic traumatic encephalopathy (CTE).
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@aO]qD@SOUqD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,368,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1783765122
OL,3,CEngland World Cup winner Nobby Stiles
OL,4,Cdied with brain injury, court hears
OL,6,FHis daughter Hayley McQueen said
OL,7,FEngland's 1966 World Cup winning team
OL,8,Fhad now been "pretty much wiped out"
OL,9,Fby neurodegenerative disease.
OL,11,FThe FA co-funded with the Professional
OL,12,FFootballers' Association (PFA) a 2019
OL,13,Fstudy that found footballers were
OL,14,Fthree-and-a-half times more likely to
OL,15,Fdie of neurodegenerative disease than
OL,16,Fage-matched members of the general
OL,17,Fpopulation.
OL,19,FThe FA is phasing out all heading in
OL,20,Fyouth football up to under-11s by 2026.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
